<h1 style="text-align:left;">
<span style="font-weight: 400;">BambooHR is hiring a </span><br>Remote SMB Sales Director Inside Sales </h1>
<div class="markdown">\nWhat You'll Do\n\nHave you experienced sales teams where management can be very political, your voice isn’t heard, or it’s all about the dollar sign and nothing else matters? Those can be challenging environments to excel in. Our leadership team refuses to have the mentality of ‘it’s my way or the highway’. Our executive sales leader has the mindset that everyone should be heard, and they listen because that is how we grow and find success. There is also peace of mind here because we have never endured a layoff at BambooHR, even during COVID.&nbsp;\n\nIn 2022 we are continuing to grow exponentially at BambooHR, which is very exciting! This role will be in addition to our incredible sales leadership team. Your role will be to help your team of sales managers reach monthly sales goals and with their development to maximize their sales potential. We will depend on you to coach and train up your sales managers and their teams as they grow here. Don’t worry, we do have an exceptional training program that all of our sales team goes through in their first few weeks of getting hired. Not to mention, the sales coaches, trainers, and resources you’ll have to utilize. In addition, you’ll work with the rest of the leadership team on operational projects, strategic plans, and overall department growth.&nbsp;\n\nWe know that the proof is in the pudding, so if you are curious what it’s like to be a part of this incredible team, then check out this video: BambooHR’s Sales Team\n\nYou will:\n\n\nLead, develop and manage a group of Sales Managers and their teams of Account Executives in the small to medium size market&nbsp;\n\nDesign and implement sales forecasting plans for Managers and Account Executives to meet and exceed revenue goals on a weekly, monthly and annual basis and design and implement sales plans to attain these targets.&nbsp;\n\nPartner and build relationships with cross-functional teams across the organization to streamline communication and drive results.&nbsp;\n\nMultiply yourself; You will train and mentor Sales Managers to become better leaders by mentoring and coaching them to support their career development\n\nCollaborate with other directors and with other teams and share innovation and best practices with the team\n\nYou will act as the sales champion by taking active part in supporting team members with larger deals and be a second voice to help get deals across the finish line\n\nCollaborate with Sales Managers to train and motivate team members by analyzing various data points to determine opportunities for your team's development and identify critical behaviors that lead to success and coach to replicate those behaviors in your reps.\n\nManage headcount (team structures, understanding capacity, planning with HR for future headcount needs) to build and hire a stellar sales team\n\n&nbsp;Take ownership of the culture (as measured by ENPS) and build strong relationships with managers and reps to help mold the team moral\n\nPrevent, manage and own team attrition,&nbsp; HR Escalations and performance improvement plans\n\n\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWhat We’ll Love About You\n\n\n3-5+&nbsp; years of experience as an Account Executive in the SMB SaaS industry with a proven track record of success\n\n2-3+&nbsp; years managing sales leadership and their teams in the SaaS (software as a service) industry.\n\nStrong Salesforce knowledge and experience&nbsp;\n\nDemonstrated&nbsp; experience in building motivating sales teams, analyzing sales trends, growing pipeline, and monitoring performance to hit revenue targets&nbsp;\n\nDemonstrated experience as a team-building leader, capable of rallying support from both direct and indirect staff to drive shared positive results&nbsp;\n\nYou have the ability to paint a vision and get buy-in through collaboration, persuasion and and mentorship/coaching skills\n\nYou have excellent written and verbal communication skills\n\nHighly driven, proactive individual with an execution focus and a strong sense of urgency and a belief in BambooHR’s mission. You go beyond relationship management&nbsp;\n\nYou have expert knowledge in various solution-selling methodologies and best practices with a proven track record of selling in the SMB SaaS industry\n\n\n\n\nWhat Will Make Us REALLY Love you\n\n\nExperience in managing groups of sales leadership in the SMB SaaS space\n\nYou have expert knowledge and experience in Salesforce\n\nYou thrive under the responsibility to train, motivate, inspire, and hold others accountable\n\nYou maintain a balance of being a true team-player as well as having a competitive edge&nbsp;\n\nYou have a positive attitude, are coachable and have proven ability to take and implement feedback&nbsp; (training, resiliency, appreciate the growth from adversity)\n\nYou have the ability to engage and communicate with reps in a positive and approachable way\n\nYou have a good command of your time and prioritize effectively the tasks that are consistently thrown your way\n\nThe ability to use candor in providing constructive feedback while being great at recognizing the positives and potential in people\n\n\n \n\n#Salary and compensation\n
No salary data published by company so we estimated salary based on similar jobs related to SaaS, Senior, Sales, Design, Marketing, Digital Nomad, Consulting, API, Jira, Python, Testing, JavaScript, Cloud, Linux, iOS, Analyst, Finance, Ruby, Engineer, Backend, Salesforce, HR and Excel jobs that are similar:\n\n
$60,000 — $120,000/year\n
\n\n#Location\nSalt Lake City, Utah, United States<br>
</div>
</div>
